'''''Three Early Poems''''' collects three [[Index:Poems by J.R.R. Tolkien|poems]] by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] first published in the 1920s:

*"[[The Man in the Moon Stayed Up Too Late|The Cat and the Fiddle]]" - from ''[[Yorkshire Poetry]]''
*"[[The Princess Ní]]" - from ''[[Leeds University Verse 1914-24]]''
*"[[An Evening in Tavrobel]]" - from ''[[Leeds University Verse 1914-24]]''

The pamphlet was privately printed in a numbered edition of ten copies.<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://www.tolkienbooks.net/php/details.php?reference=11890|articlename=Three Early Poems. 1991|dated=|website=TB|accessed=12 July 2012}}</ref>
